            <p:rationale>IT is responsible for availability and reliability of provided IT services and underlying technology. To be able to ensure an anticipated level of availability and reliability, the services, applications and technology must be continuously monitored for their stability, availability, events and performance. If these are not monitored, the risk of unplanned outages, incidents affecting end users, and financial losses caused by poor performance of business processes, increases dramatically.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>Hardware and software must be selected to enable adequate monitoring. Monitoring capability must be designed and incorporated into all applications and their components.
Minimum monitoring requirements must be defined, designed, documented, and followed.
Monitoring mechanisms, policies, and routines should be reflected in the architecture.
Processes of design, development, and implementation of monitoring must be developed and put in place.
A close relationship between SLA and monitoring teams should be enforced.</p:implications>
